from system kalki dasa subject bhagavad-gitum text trai-gunya-visaya veda nistrai-gunyo bhavarjuna nirdvandvo nitya-sattva-stho niryoga-ksema atmavan trai-gunya pertain to the three mode of material nature visayah on the subject matter vedah vedic literature nistrai-gunyah transcendental to the three mode of material nature bhava be arjuna o arjuna nirdvandvah without duality nitya-sattva-sthah in a pure state of spiritual existence niryoga-ksemah free from idea of gain and protection atma-van establish in the self translation the veda deal mainly with the subject of the three mode of material nature o arjuna become transcendental to these three mode be free from all duality and from all anxiety for gain and safety and be establish in the self purport all material activity involve action and reaction in the three mode of material nature they be mean for fruitive result which cause bondage in the material world the veda deal mostly with fruitive activity to gradually elevate the general public from the field of sense gratification to a position on the transcendental plane arjuna a a student and friend of lord krsna be advise to raise himself to the transcendental position of vedantum philosophy where in the begin there be brahma-jijnasa or question on the supreme transcendence all the live entity who be in the material world be struggle very hard for existence for them the lord after creation of the material world give the vedic wisdom advise how to live and get rid of the material entanglement when the activity for sense gratification namely the karma-kanda chapter be finish then the chance for spiritual realization be offer in the form of the upanisad which be part of different veda a the bhagavad-gitum be a part of the fifth veda namely the mahabharatum the upanisad mark the begin of transcendental life a long a the material body exist there be action and reaction in the material mode one ha to learn tolerance in the face of duality such a happiness and distres or cold and warmth and by tolerate such duality become free from anxiety regard gain and los thi transcendental position be achieve in full krsna consciousnes when one be fully dependent on the good will of krsna bhagavad-gitum a it be book of bhaktivedantum swami do forget to chant hare krishna hare krishna krishna krishna hare hare hare rama hare rama rama rama hare hare kalki infoline bb aiken south carolina usa system 